dcterms:description: The Neurofinder training datasets contain 60K images with 7K neurons labeled by researchers at four labs with various experimental settings. They are highly heterogeneous in appearance, making it difficult to define a characteristic neuron.
dcterms:title: Neurofinder Datasets

dcterms:description: The St. Jude datasets contain GCaMP6f-expressing neurons from the auditory cortex, a cortical region not represented in Neurofinder, and have bounding box ground truth masks instead of precise outlines.
dcterms:title: St. Jude Datasets
